      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Bakes the generated color into proper PBR texture maps on the mesh, combining the trimesh, textured voxelgrid, and original_mesh. \n\nOutputs the final textured trimesh ready for export.\n\ntexture_size (4096): output texture resolution. 4096 = high detail for close-ups/renders; drop to 2048 for game assets or lighter files."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        -447.8499915184054,
        -637.8548812593057
      ],
      "size": [
        307.57738831345955,
        337.6563491495082
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 3,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "The main 3D generation step.\n\nTakes model_config + conditioning and produces the mesh (plus shape_slat/subs for downstream nodes).\n\nseed / control after generate: fixed reuses the same seed for repeatable results; switch to randomize to explore variations.\n\n*ss_ (sparse structure)**: builds the coarse shape.\n\n*shape_ **: refines geometry.\n\nguidance_strength (~6.5): how strongly it follows your image — higher = more faithful but can over-constrain; lower = more creative.\n\nguidance_rescale (~0.05): stabilizer, leave as-is.\n\nsampling_steps (12): quality vs speed — raise for more detail, lower for faster gen.\n\nmax_tokens: mesh complexity ceiling; lower it if you hit VRAM limits."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        396.7278088723417,
        -626.3793930705856
      ],
      "size": [
        310.9090631658379,
        362.42423317649144
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 4,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Cleans and optimizes the raw trimesh into a production-ready mesh. Runs after generation, before texturing/export.\n\nremesh / remesh_band: rebuilds topology for cleaner, more even geometry.\n\nremove_inner_faces (true): deletes hidden internal faces — keep on for lighter meshes.\n\ntarget_face_count (500k): polygon budget. Lower it for game/real-time assets, raise for high-detail renders.\n\nfloater_threshold (0.001): removes stray disconnected bits; raise if you see floating debris.\n\nweld_vertices / weld_digits: merges duplicate verts to close seams; higher digits = stricter matching.\n\nchart_*: controls UV unwrapping quality for texturing — defaults are tuned, leave unless UVs look off."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
