        "Sets the core 3D model config. resolution: mesh detail (512 fast / 1024 balanced / 1536 max).\n\nprecision: leave auto (picks best for your GPU).\n\nattn_backend: leave auto. Downstream nodes read this config.\n\ncascade = two-pass generation (coarse mesh → refinement) for higher detail; slower and more VRAM than the single-pass option at the same resolution. Can be more glitchy.\n\nHigher resolution = sharper geometry but more VRAM and time."
