      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Loads images from a folder, one per run, to auto-process a whole directory through the pipeline.\n\npath: folder to pull from (e.g. input/ or an absolute path).\n\nmode: incremental_image steps to the next image each run; \n\nsingle_image loads just the one at index.\ncontrol after generate = increment: advances automatically each queue run — set ComfyUI's batch count to your image count to process the whole folder.\npattern (*): filter files, e.g. *.png.\nindex: which image to start from (0 = first).\nOutputs image + filename_text (the file's name).\n\n\nFor best TRELLIS results:\n\nAim for roughly 1024×1024, or anywhere in the ~512–2048 range. The subject should fill most of the frame at that size. Square-ish is ideal since the model works from a centered subject.\n\nSingle, clearly-defined subject — one object centered in frame, not a scene or collage.\n\nClean/simple background (plain white or solid). \n\nBusy backgrounds confuse the shape; the Remove Background node helps but a clean input is better.\n\nFull object visible — no cropping or cut-off edges for better generation.\n\nEven, diffuse lighting — avoid harsh shadows, blown-out highlights, or strong reflections that hide geometry.\n\n3/4 or front-facing angle shows the most surface detail; flat side-on or top-down views give the model less to work with.\n\nSharp and well-lit — blur, low resolution, or dark images produce mushy meshes.\n\nAvoid transparent/reflective materials (glass, chrome, water) — they're hard to reconstruct accurately."
      ],
